Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.DemonologistClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Beginning at 1st level, a demonologist gains the ability to cast a small number of arcane spells. To cast a spell, the demonologist must have a Charisma score of at least 10 + the spell's level, so a demonologist with a Charisma of 10 or lower cannot cast these spells. Demonologist bonus spells are based on Charisma, and saving throws against these spells have a DC of 10 + spell level + Charisma modifier. The demonologist's spell list appears below; a demonologist has access to any spell on the list and need not prepare those spells ahead of time, just like a sorcerer. A demonologist casts spells just as a sorcerer does.	KEY:Demonologist ~ Spells				DEFINE:Caster_Level_Demonologist|0	DEFINE:Caster_Level_BL_Demonologist|0				BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|Demonologist|Caster_Level_Demonologist	BONUS:VAR|Caster_Level_Demonologist|DemonologistLVL+Caster_Level_Bonus	BONUS:VAR|Caster_Level_BL_Demonologist|charbonusto(PCLEVEL","Demonologist")	BONUS:VAR|Caster_Level_Highest__Arcane|Caster_Level_Demonologist+Caster_Level_BL_Demonologist|TYPE=Base														SORTKEY:Class_Demonologist	SOURCEPAGE:BoVD	
Charm Demon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.DemonologistClassFeatures.SpecialAttack.SpellLike	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A 1st-level demonologist can attempt to charm a chaotic evil outsider, as described in the charm person spell, once per day. The demon does not get to use its spell resistance, though it can make a saving throw as normal (DC 11 + demonologist's Cha modifier).	KEY:Demonologist ~ Charm Demon																		SPELLS:Innate|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=DemonologistLVL|Charm Person,11+CHA								SORTKEY:Class_Demonologist	SOURCEPAGE:BoVD	
Quasit Familiar	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.DemonologistClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A 2nd-level demonologist gains a quasit as a familiar, whether he wants it or not. If the demonologist already has a familiar, the quasit devours it and takes its place, but the character suffers no experience point loss. The quasit is treated as a normal familiar, using the class level of the demonologist as the master's level (see the Familiars section in Chapter 3 of the Player's Handbook for familiar abilities).	KEY:Demonologist ~ Quasit Familiar				DEFINE:DemonologistQuasitFamiliarLVL|0					BONUS:VAR|DemonologistQuasitFamiliarLVL|1|TYPE=Base																	SORTKEY:Class_Demonologist	SOURCEPAGE:BoVD	
Summoning Mastery	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.DemonologistClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When a demonologist of 3rd level or higher casts a summon monster spell, it is treated as the equivalent spell of two levels higher for purposes of summoning chaotic evil creatures. For example, a demonologist refers to the summon monster IV list for chaotic evil outsiders when casting summon monster II. At 6th level, the demonologist refers to the summoning list three levels higher than the one for the summon monster spell he is casting. At 9th level, the demonologist refers to the list four levels higher.	KEY:Demonologist ~ Summoning Mastery																										SORTKEY:Class_Demonologist	SOURCEPAGE:BoVD	
Resistances	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.DemonologistClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A demonologist who reaches 4th level gains acid resistance 10, cold resistance 10, fire resistance 10, and electricity resistance 20.	KEY:Demonologist ~ Resistances									BONUS:VAR|AcidResistanceBonus,ColdResistanceBonus,FireResistanceBonus,ElectricityResistanceBonus|10|TYPE=Resistance									ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Resistance to Acid|Resistance to Cold|Resistance to Fire|Resistance to Electricity								SORTKEY:Class_Demonologist	SOURCEPAGE:BoVD	
Poison Immunity	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.DemonologistClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A 5thlevel demonologist is immune to poison.	KEY:Demonologist ~ Poison Immunity																		ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Immunity to Poison								SORTKEY:Class_Demonologist	SOURCEPAGE:BoVD	
Hold Person	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.DemonologistClassFeatures.SpecialAttack.SpellLike	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A 7th-level demonologist can attempt to hold a chaotic evil outsider, as described in the hold person spell, once per day. The demon does not get to use its spell resistance, though it can make a saving throw as normal (DC 12 + demonologist's Cha modifier).	KEY:Demonologist ~ Hold Demon																		SPELLS:Innate|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=DemonologistLVL|Charm Person,12+CHA								SORTKEY:Class_Demonologist	SOURCEPAGE:BoVD	
